==English==
===Etymology===
Old English ''[[wæpengetæc|wǣpenġetæc]]'' from Old Norse ''[[vápnatak]]'', ''[[vápn]]'' weapon + ''[[taka]]'' take.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/'wɒpənteɪk/}}

===Noun===
'''wapentake'''
#an [[administrative]] [[subdivision]] in [[northern]] [[English]] [[counties]], developed under [[Norse]] influence, and corresponding to [[hundred]]s in the rest of England.

